31/01/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Restructuring the judiciary and police, as well as strengthening the fight against organised and economic crime, are the government's top priorities over the next six months, according to Prime Minister Sali Berisha. He presented the government's programme to parliament on Monday (30 January), vowing in particular to impose stiffer legal penalties for drug trafficking and tax fraud. (Focus - 31/01/06)
